My 12 week training camp for #WrestleMania has been intense and unlike anything I‚Äôve ever done. 
Pushing myself physically, mentally and psychologically to places I‚Äôve never gone. 

The men I‚Äôm wrestling this weekend at WrestleMania are the best in the world. 
My respect for them is boundless.
My love for pro wrestling is forever. 

Honored to share the ring, go to war in our squared circle and entrain the fans. 

Here‚Äôs a raw and uncut look at one of my final training sessions this week. 

Audaces Fortuna Iuvat,

- Final Boss

Huge congratulations to my brother and tattoo artist @yomicoart on his spectacular, first of its kind Tattoo Seminar and Master Class! 

Yomico, what a beautiful opportunity you offered for artists from all over the world ‚ÄîUSA, Chile, Colombia, Italy, Spain, Canada, and more ‚Äî who all came together to learn, grow, connect on the tattoo art we all love. 

Our @zoaenergy was proud to be a sponsor of this event, giving all the artists the mental clarity, energy and balance to fuel them during this incredible seminar. 

So much more to look forward to together in the future, Brother.
üñ§‚úçüèæ

And thank you for that big @Teremana toast at end! 

Salud‚Äô ü•É

#GlobalTattooConference
#TheArtThatLeavesWithYou 
#YomicoTMC

node.text:
Why buy the @XFL? 

1) Because I love the game of football. 

2) There‚Äôs 53 players on an @NFL roster ‚Äî I was always that 54th player. 
Solid player, but not good enough to make the cut. 

3) So now I can create opportunities for other players to get after it and achieve their goals and live their dreams. 

4) We want to grow the game of football. 

#94 on the field üí™üèæ
#1 in your heart üòâ

This is the XFL. 

#owner 
@espn 
@espngreeny 
@danygarciaco

node.text:
As promised we had big and exciting news today for our @XFL as we announced our Head Coach line up for our 2023 season üèà 

These Head Coaches are Super Bowl Champions, National Champions and @NFL Hall of Famers. 

Committed to winning, establishing our XFL culture and growing the game of football. 

Wade Phillips 
Rod Woodson 
Bob Stoops 
Hines Ward 
Anthony Becht
Jim Haslett 
Reggie Barlow 

And one of the greatest college football players of all time, and I‚Äôm singling him out because he‚Äôs an FSU guy - Terrell Buckley
(Go Canes üôåüèæüòâ) 

Appreciate our friends @espngreeny @getupespn & @ESPN for helping us launch our big news. 

Step by step we build. 

Welcome to the XFL. 

~ dj 
Owner üèà
#xfl2023

node.text:
Love this ‚ù§Ô∏è
What a FUN moment captured here as students of APALACHEE HIGH SCHOOL in Winder, GA started PALMING MY BALD HEAD like I was their DAD rubbing it for good luck, when we were taking this selfie ü§≥üèæ üòÇüòÇüòÇüë®üèæ‚Äçü¶≤‚úãüèΩ

Unimaginable tragedy that these kids, their families and community have gone thru with the recent mass shooting at their high school. 

To see them smile big with joy and have some fun, made my heart full. 

Their healing journey. 

#WeAreOneApalachee 

üì∏ @thisisamandaw

Sometimes one of the best paths to begin the healing journey is through our smiles, laughter and joy. 

I was blessed this past week to have the APALACHEE HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL TEAM come visit me at the production soundstages I‚Äôve been filming at here in Atlanta, Georgia. 

As the world knows, Apalachee High School in Winder, GA, has endured the unimaginable tragedy of a mass shooting. 

I didn‚Äôt know what to expect when I walked in to meet them - I was absolutely BLOWN AWAY by their spirit and energy. I looked these kids in their eyes and hugged ‚Äòem - I know they‚Äôre in great pain, but man are they resilient and staying strong. 

It was as if they just needed a reason, an opportunity to just ‚Äúlet it all go‚Äù in this moment. 

As we said goodbyes, the last kid I hugged said, ‚Äúwe needed this Rock‚Äù 
(so did I) 

I can‚Äôt begin to imagine what these players and all the students, teachers & staff of Apalachee High are going through right now, but I‚Äôm here in any and every way I can be - to give my support and love to them and their families as they begin their healing journey. 

God bless you all. 

We Are One Apalachee. 

ps, I‚Äôm in touch with Coach Hancock and as promised, I‚Äôll be there for your first home game.

üì∏ @thisisamandaw
üì∏ @hhgarcia41 
üì∏ @masistills

Burnin‚Äô the midnight candle in the IP üïØÔ∏è 
Bench press at the END of my chest training. 
Depending on how I feel, I‚Äôll often end training major parts (chest, back, legs) with a compound movement that very strict and slow with a 3:1 tempo (3 second negative, 1 sec pause). 
Great activation and because I‚Äôm fatigued at this point, it forces me to really concentrate on mind muscle connection - and not be a little bitch because of the pain üòÇüí™üèæ 

Give bench (or any press) wide grip pull ups/downs and squats a try at the end of your training. You‚Äôll make some good progress + you also wont need to load the bar up with a lot of weight. 

#ironparadise üïØÔ∏è

I know, I know this may sound corny‚Ä¶

but you guys hear me say this all the time when it comes to things like this‚Ä¶

meeting people and hearing about their journeys of weight loss, mental health struggles, fitness, dealing with loss, anxiety, depression, hard times etc etc 

moments Iike this become my profound reminder that this is the best part of fame‚Ä¶ 

Keep up the great work Jonny Cleasby, not only have you changed your life, but your journey will change many lives who you‚Äôll go on to touch, as you roll on down the road of life. 

Happy birthday dude, go crush cake & tequila üòâüç∞ü•É

~ dj
